  "id": "hiragana",
  "name": "Hiragana (gojūon)",
  "color": "#ff9f43",
  "dual": true,
  "lang": "ja",
  "description": "The 46 basic hiragana. Each kana is tested both ways — recall the reading from the symbol and the symbol from the reading — tracked separately.",
  "primerTitle": "Reading hiragana",
  "primer": "**Hiragana** is the basic Japanese phonetic script — one symbol per *syllable* (a sound, not a letter). The 46 basic kana are organised in the **gojūon** (\"fifty sounds\") order: the five vowels first, then each consonant crossed with those vowels. Learn them row by row; the romaji below is what each card asks for.\n\n| | a | i | u | e | o |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **–** | あ a | い i | う u | え e | お o |\n| **k** | か ka | き ki | く ku | け ke | こ ko |\n| **s** | さ sa | し **shi** | す su | せ se | そ so |\n| **t** | た ta | ち **chi** | つ **tsu** | て te | と to |\n| **n** | な na | に ni | ぬ nu | ね ne | の no |\n| **h** | は ha | ひ hi | ふ **fu** | へ he | ほ ho |\n| **m** | ま ma | み mi | む mu | め me | も mo |\n| **y** | や ya | | ゆ yu | | よ yo |\n| **r** | ら ra | り ri | る ru | れ re | ろ ro |\n| **w** | わ wa | | | | を **wo** |\n| **n** | ん **n** | | | | |\n\n**Irregular readings** (don't follow the consonant+vowel pattern): し = *shi*, ち = *chi*, つ = *tsu*, ふ = *fu*. These are the ones most often missed.\n\n**Special kana:**\n- **ん** is the only standalone consonant (*n*); it never begins a word.\n- **を** (*wo*, pronounced *o*) is used only as the object particle.\n- **は** is read *wa* when it marks the topic, **へ** is read *e* when it marks direction — but as kana their base readings are *ha* and *he*.\n\nThe **y-row** and **w-row** have gaps (no やぃ, no ゐ/ゑ here), so only the kana shown exist in this deck.",
  "categories": {
    "v": "Vowels",
    "k": "K-row",
    "s": "S-row",
    "t": "T-row",
    "n": "N-row",
    "h": "H-row",
    "m": "M-row",
    "y": "Y-row",
    "r": "R-row",
    "w": "W-row + ん"
  },
